    <section id="vConnect">
        <h2>vConnect</h2>
        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="left-column">
            <p>vConnect is a lightweight integration solution that enables seamless 
                file-based data exchange over HTTP. As a complement to the SAP Integration Suite,
                it fills the gap where no native file adapter exists. vConnect allows businesses 
                to transfer files via HTTP endpoints, serving as an alternative to sFTP or other 
                traditional file transfer methods. This makes it ideal for scenarios requiring simple, 
                secure, and efficient file-to-HTTP or HTTP-to-file integrations</p>
        </div>

        <div class="right-column">
            <p>vConnect is part of the free and open-source <b>vIntegrationTools</b>, a collection of 
                utilities designed to simplify SAP and cloud integrations. Developed to bridge gaps 
                in standard integration capabilities, these tools provide flexible solutions for various use cases. 
                vConnect and other components are available on GitHub, allowing businesses to leverage, 
                customize, and contribute to the project. Explore more at:
                <a href="https://github.com/stefanzimara/vIntegrationTools" target="_blank">ðŸ”— [GitHub - vIntegrationTools]</a></p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="vConnect-status">
        <h2>vConnect Status</h2>
        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="left-column">
                <table> <tr><th>Eigenschaft</th><th>Wert</th></tr> <tr><td><b>Server-Zeit</b></td><td><%= data.server_time %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Server-IP</b></td><td><%= data.server_ip %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Client-IP</b></td><td><%= data.client_ip %></td></tr> <tr>
                    <td><b>HTTP-Version</b></td><td><%= data.http_version %></td></tr>
                    <tr><td><b>Request-Methode</b></td><td><%= data.request_method %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Aufgerufene URL</b></td><td><%= data.requested_url %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Protokoll</b></td><td><%= data.protocol %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Browser / User-Agent</b></td><td><%= data.browser_user_agent %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Referrer</b></td>
                        <td><%= data.referrer %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Encoding</b></td><td><%= data.encoding %></td></tr> <tr><td><b>Spracheinstellungen</b></td><td><%= data.language %></td></tr> </table>
    
            </div>

             <div class="right-column">
             <pre><%= JSON.stringify(data.request_headers, null, 2) %></pre>
            </div>
        </div>

    </section>
    
    <section id="documentation">
        <h2>Documentation</h2>

        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="left-column">
                <p>
                    <table>
                    <thead>
                    <tr>
                    <th>Command</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm install</code></td>
                    <td>Installs all required dependencies</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm start</code></td>
                    <td>Starts the vConnect application</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm stop</code></td>
                    <td>Stops the running vConnect instance</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm run restart</code></td>
                    <td>Restarts the application</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm run build</code></td>
                    <td>Builds the application for production use</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>npm run dev</code></td>
                    <td>Starts vConnect in development mode</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>docker-compose up -d</code></td>
                    <td>Starts vConnect as a Docker container (detached)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>docker-compose down</code></td>
                    <td>Stops and removes the Docker container</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>pm2 start vconnect.js</code></td>
                    <td>Starts vConnect using PM2 for process management</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>pm2 stop vconnect</code></td>
                    <td>Stops the vConnect instance managed by PM2</td>
                    </tr>
                    </tbody>
                    </table>
                    </p>
            </div>
            <div class="right-column">
                <p><table>
                    <thead>
                    <tr>
                    <th>Config Key</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>PORT</code></td>
                    <td>Defines the port on which vConnect runs (default: 3000)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>HTTP_ENDPOINT</code></td>
                    <td>Specifies the HTTP endpoint for file uploads</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>FILE_STORAGE_PATH</code></td>
                    <td>Sets the local directory for storing uploaded files</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>MAX_FILE_SIZE</code></td>
                    <td>Limits the maximum upload size (e.g., 50MB)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>ALLOWED_EXTENSIONS</code></td>
                    <td>Defines allowed file extensions (e.g., .csv, .xml, .json)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>LOG_LEVEL</code></td>
                    <td>Sets the logging level (info, debug, error)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>AUTH_TOKEN</code></td>
                    <td>Optional: Enables authentication for API requests</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td><code>DELETE_AFTER_PROCESSING</code></td>
                    <td>Determines if files should be deleted after processing (true/false)</td>
                    </tr>
                    </tbody>
                    </table>
                     
                    <p>For more details and advanced configuration, visit the <a href="https://github.com/stefanzimara/vIntegrationTools/wiki" target="_blank">GitHub Wiki</a>.</p>
                    
                </p>                    
            </div>
        </div>
